name: Tim Ryan
tweet: “When Democrats work together, organize together, and vote together, we’re unstoppable. They said it couldn’t be done in Alabama and Virginia and Pennsylvania and Georgia, but we proved to this nation and to ourselves that there’s nothing we can’t do.” #SaveOurCities

name: Tim Ryan
tweet: “We can’t meet the challenges of our time if we’re divided. Division is the enemy of progress—not just for working people, but for our nation. We can’t wait for the powerful and privileged few to make this country better. It’s got to be us. All of us.” #SaveOurCities

name: Tim Ryan
tweet: “So if anyone asks who we are and what we’re for, tell them Democrats are the Party of And. The Party of Jobs and Justice. The Party of Equality and the Economy.” #SaveOurCities

name: Tim Ryan
tweet: “We need to put quality back in equality of opportunity, ensuring every child in every zip code gets a high-quality education. The kind of education that will prepare our children to compete globally and get good jobs that pay a livable, dignifying wage.” #SaveOurCities

name: Tim Ryan
tweet: “Economic injustice is a drain on the entire nation, but especially people of color. That is a social justice issue AND an economic justice issue. They cannot be seen in isolation. In fact, we cannot achieve either without achieving both.” #SaveOurCities

name: Tim Ryan
tweet: “Politicians often talk about our unfair economic system, one that separates people into haves and have-nots. But we fail to mention how this separation has been decided by race since our country’s founding. Systemic racism is the enemy of economic empowerment.” #SaveOurCities

name: Tim Ryan
tweet: “As Democrats, we believe everyone deserved a fair shake in life. But a fair shake means more than having a few extra dollars in your pocket. It’s more than having a job. It’s about rewarding hard work and getting ahead.” #SaveOurCities

name: Tim Ryan
tweet: “I reject that premise, that false choice. I believe we can be both. And if the Democratic Party is to be true to its mission, we as Democrats MUST do both. We can’t be bullied into being the Party of Or, we must become the Party of And.” #SaveOurCities

name: Tim Ryan
tweet: “Some people concerned about our party have internalized this conflict. They say that we, too, must make a choice. Do we fight for the voters who left us, or the ones who remained loyal? They say we can be the Party of Jobs or Equality, but we can’t be both.” #SaveOurCities

name: Tim Ryan
tweet: “It’s tempting to dismiss the people who seem too different from us, whose interests seem at odds with our own. We must resist this temptation. The strength we derive from diversity is turned into weakness through division.” #SaveOurCities

name: Tim Ryan
tweet: “But progress requires power. And right now, Democrats have little. By every measure and at every level, Republicans have a firm grip on the levers of power. Without the votes, without the seats, without a majority, Democrats can only sit on the sidelines.” #SaveOurCities

name: Tim Ryan
tweet: “We have states where it’s harder to register to vote and cast a ballot than to buy a gun. We have a tax system made for millionaires and billionaires, paid for on the backs of the squeezed and struggling.” #SaveOurCities

tweet: “No organization has fought harder for underserved communities than the @NatUrbanLeague. Since 1910, you’ve challenged our nation to live up to its potential, its promise, and its principles. 108 years later, that mission is more important than ever.” #SaveOurCities
